President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 6, 2011, as Military Spouse Appreciation Day. In his proclamation, he recognizes the important role that military spouses play in supporting and caring for service members. He emphasizes that military families are called to serve when a member of the Armed Forces is deployed, and their readiness is crucial to the readiness of the troops. The President commends the efforts of First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden in their initiative, "Joining Forces," which aims to address the unique challenges faced by military families and provide them with opportunities and support. He urges Americans to show their appreciation for military spouses by reaching out to them in various ways, such as offering help with household maintenance and childcare, and encouraging their community involvement and career development. The proclamation concludes by calling upon the people of the United States to honor military spouses with appropriate ceremonies and activities.